The governor of Ebonyi State, Dave Umahi, and his Deputy, Dr Kelechi Igwe have removed from office.  The duo were sacked by a Federal High Court in Abuja today. The court sacked the governor and his deputy on account of their unlawful defection from the Peoples Democratic Party PDP to the All Progressives Congress (APC). The court declared their defection unlawful, unconstitutional, null and void and ordered them to immediately vacate their offices. Justice Inyang Ekwo in a judgment on Tuesday ordered Umahi and his deputy to immediately stop holding themselves out as Governor and Deputy Governor of Ebonyi State. The judge held that the votes that brought them to office belonged to the PDP and cannot hold on to the votes having elected to jettison the party that nominated them. Justice Ekwo also held that the votes cast for PDP in the March 9, 2019 governorship election are not transferrable to the APC that failed in the election.  source The Peoples Democratic Party has applied to have Zamfara Deputy Governor, Alhaji Mahadi Aliyu Gusau's name removed from a suit seeking to unseat him and the Governor Bello Muhammad Matawalle. The PDP made the move on Friday after approaching the Federal High Court. The party had accused the duo of… In "News" A suit seeking to remove Dave Umahi as governor of Ebonyi state for defecting to the All Progressives Congress from the Peoples Democratic Party has been dismissed. The suit was dismissed by an Abakaliki Division of the Ebonyi State High Court, on Monday. According to the court, the governor did… In "News" A lawsuit has been filed against Governor Bello Matawalle and his deputy by the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) on Monday at the Federal High Court for defecting to the ruling All Progressive Congress, APC. Also slated for removal from office is the Deputy Governor of the state, Alhaji Mahadi Aliyu… In "News"